  "lyrics": "Oh yeah, you see me on your mind all the time\nOn the dashboard of life There's no telling where the stats go\nAm I doing it right? Am I making it always harder\nOn myself for the things I want and all I see\nYeah I'm trying to take accountability\nAnd see me on the dashboard of life\nI'm getting all my API calls right\nOn the dashboard of life\nI'm finding where my problems begin\nI gotta put a little error handling in the moment\nMake it know that I can come back to the things that were trouble for me\nAnd make them a part of my history\nGo past the level and go past the line\nThat's what I say every motherfucking time\nBut for real, for real I'm checking this\nNew dash dashboard of life\nAll my knobs going in the right direction\nI'm talk in beatmaps\nTo the bar graphs, to the pie graphs\nCan I see where my data direction is going\nAnd do I want to share that with the world\nKnowing that everybody judges\nAnd it's narcissistic moments out there\nEverybody taking life for granted\nAnd wondering about the things you can get here\nThat you can't take to the next level\nAnd I'm sorry if I said that and you don't believe\nBut trust me, there's the metrics on ya yeah\nDashboard of life\nThe moment you check yourself in the mirror\nOn the dashboard of life\nDashboard of your only life\nYou better pay attention to the numbers that tell you\nYou better pay attention to the things they tell you\nYou better make your own mind up\nBefore you only crash and burn in this\nChecking of yourself in the mirror\nDon't make it so you wince so much\nThere's still time on the dashboard of life\nYou're gonna find which way and what matters to you",
  "lyricsSegments": [
    {
      "end": 9.739999771118164,
      "text": "Oh yeah, you see me on your mind all the time",
